HEADWORD: Reconcilable
<hw>Rec"on*ci`la*ble</hw> <pr>(r?k"?n*s?`l?*b'l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>r⟦eacute⟧conciliable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Capable of
being reconciled; <as>as, <ex>reconcilable</ex> adversaries; an act
<ex>reconciable</ex> with previous acts.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The different accounts of the numbers of ships are
<qex>reconcilable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Rec"on*ci`la*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Rec"on*ci`la*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
